A RESOLUTION
1 Congratulating and honoring William Edwards; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, William Edwards, a junior at the University of North Georgia (UNG), has been
3 named the university's presidential fellow to the Center for the Study of the Presidency and
4 Congress (CSPC) for the 2024-2025 academic year, a prestigious program that includes
5 monthly seminars and a multi-day leadership conference in Washington, D.C.; and
6 WHEREAS, Edwards, a cadet major in the UNG Boar's Head Brigade and Brigade S-4, is
7 pursing a degree in history with a perfect 4.0 GPA; and
8 WHEREAS, Edwards' selection for the CSPC fellowship reflects his commitment to studying
9 the public policymaking process and fostering a deeper understanding of the presidency,
10 Congress, and their roles in addressing national changes; and
11 WHEREAS, Edwards has achieved notable academic and military accomplishments,
12 including earning an Army ROTC Scholarship, graduating from the Army Air Assault
13 School at Fort Moore and the Cadet Basic Leadership Course (CBLC), and serving as
14 commander of the Range Challenge Gold Team; and
