15 WHEREAS, Edwards has demonstrated consistent academic excellence, earning a place on
16 the UNG President's List every semester since Fall 2022, and he has further expanded his
17 education through participation in the UNG Aviation Ground School and the United States
18 Army Project GO Scholarship for studying Russian at the Strategic Language Institute; and
19 WHEREAS, Edwards, a resident of Dahlonega, Georgia, exemplifies leadership, scholarship,
20 and service in his roles as a cadet, student, and active member of the Pi Kappa Alpha
21 Fraternity; and
22 WHEREAS, Edwards will culminate his CSPC fellowship experience by authoring a
23 research paper that integrates his insights and learning; and
24 WHEREAS, Edwards credits the University of North Georgia with providing him confidence
25 and a platform to make a meaningful difference in his community and beyond.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
27 congratulate and honor William Edwards upon being named the presidential fellow to the
28 Center for the Study of the Presidency and Congress as well as extend sincere best wishes
29 for future health, happiness, and success.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
31 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to William Edwards.
